Azure Machine Learning is a cloud service that helps you build, deploy, and manage machine learning models. It provides a variety of tools and services that you can use to automate the machine learning process, from data preparation to model deployment.
Azure Machine Learning can be used by anyone who wants to build machine learning models, regardless of their experience level. It is a powerful platform that can be used to solve a variety of problems, such as fraud detection, image classification, and natural language processing.

Here are some of the key features of Azure Machine Learning:

Automated machine learning: Azure Machine Learning provides a variety of automated machine learning tools that can help you build models without having to write any code.
Managed infrastructure: Azure Machine Learning provides a managed infrastructure that takes care of the underlying hardware and software, so you can focus on building models.
Integration with other Azure services: Azure Machine Learning can be integrated with other Azure services, such as Azure Databricks and Azure Synapse Analytics, to provide a complete end-to-end machine learning solution.